After spending an off-season and a year of lock-down on his home trails in Santa Cruz, California, @r_doggystyles, aka Ryan Howard, finally flew the coop to visit a friend and check out their riding scene. With the right mix of features, banter, wildflowers, and local insight to lead the way, any place can become your next epic destination. Watch R-Dog x Beacon Hill, WA now!⁣
⁣
Video By: @mindsparkcinema / @isaacwallenn #RockShox

node.text:
To kick off our Brains Behind the Brand series, we introduce you to Jesse Jakomait, a Senior Design Engineer who has been part of the RockShox team for 11 years. Jesse's love for bikes is amplified by an engineering degree and superhuman mindset that has pushed him to set records and stand on more peaks than anyone we know. World, meet Jesse.⁣
⁣
Video By: @joeyschusler #RockShox

node.title: Brains Behind the Brand: Jesse Jakomait

What do fresh pumpkin pie and fresh feeling suspension have in common? They're both extremely satisfying and take less than an hour to make happen! Built to withstand everything the 7,960-foot singletrack descent of Pikes Peak is known for – death grip speeds, relentless rock gardens, raw corners, steep chutes, and one heck of a good time. The next evolution of single crown awesome from RockShox is here. Meet ZEB.

Video By: @mindsparkcinema #RockShoxZEB

node.text:
Becoming the first US Elite Men XC World Cup winner since 1994, @ChristopherBlevs' tactful and powerful racing was on display in the World Cup XCO Finals in Snowshoe, USA. Chris played it smart, keeping himself in the lead group and executing his attack in the last lap – crossing the finish line for his first World Cup win an impressive 9 seconds ahead of 2nd place. All in front of his friends and family. Congratulations, Chris! Way to represent the USA!⁣⁣⁣
⁣
Photos By: @michalcervenyphoto #RockShox

node.text:
A perfect weekend for @eviealicerichards to end the season on, winning World Cup XCO Finals by over a minute and a half. It wasn’t without a fight, however. @becmcconnell pushed the pace on the first two laps, eclipsing Evie until a flat required a pit stop in the tech zone. Evie pulled ahead and continued to put time into the field as she valiantly held her effort into the finish. Rebecca caught back up to the lead group, regaining her position to finish P2. Incredible work, ladies! The World Cup Overall podium speaks for itself with Evie, @jennyrissveds, @becmcconnell, and @freisina rounding out 2nd through 5th place. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣
Photos By: @rossbellphoto / @andyvathis #RockShox

The moment that changed everything. The moment that @valihoell found out she won her second World Cup. The moment she clutched the Overall Title. She never dreamed it was possible this season. But then again, her story has just begun.⁣
 ⁣
“I still don’t really get it. I’m celebrating like I did for my first World Cup podium, but now I’ve just won my second World Cup and the Overall. This season was so rough for me, and I never dreamed that this would ever happen at the end. It’s unbelievable.”⁣
⁣
Photos By: @svenmartinphoto #RockShox

node.text:
Pop the champagne. @valihoell’s gone gold to claim her first Elite Women's win of the season with a 4-second margin in Snowshoe, USA. ⁣
 ⁣
“It was wild. I had a massive crash on the first day of practice. I actually didn’t do one of the main jumps to not risk it and get home safe. So I went around it and tried to get some speed and pedal. I’m stoked, I (bleep) won my first World Cup. It’s my first double header as well. I need to save my energy for the week since we restart again tomorrow.” ⁣
 ⁣
Photos By: @svenmartinphoto #RockShox

Stay tuned for coverage all week long! ⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
With racing, comes grit and glory. After Round 7 of @world_enduro, @jackmoir_ has experienced both this season. Entering Crans-Montana as the Series Overall leader, Jack sustained a shoulder injury in Saturday's Prologue but entered Sunday's stages knowing that valuable points were still on the line. Giving it his all to cross the finish in 10th place, Jack helped carry @canyon_cllctv’s lead in the Team Rankings alongside his teammates @dim_tordo and @zemanelborges.⁣
 ⁣
In the Pro Women's race, @hatt1e_harnden charged her way to 4th place overall, after a sizable crash in the Prologue followed by winning Stage 2. @isabeau_c rode consistently through all five gnarly stages to take 6th place.⁣
 ⁣
Riders get a break this week before Round 8 in Finale Ligure on September 18. In the meantime, World Cup Finals kick off this week in Snowshoe, USA. ⁣
⁣
Photos By: @svenmartinphoto #RockShox

 ⁣⁣
Round 7 of @world_enduro kicks off Saturday with the Prologue followed by race day on Sunday. We've seen some of the tightest racing to date and expect this weekend to be no different.⁣⁣

node.text:
Embodying the spirit of slopestyle mountain biking, @brandonsemenuk shows his creativity in his latest edit REALM. Designing four unique features, Brandon continues to push boundaries and challenge what is possible.⁣
⁣
"Like any mountain bike trail or course, you work with the given terrain to make the best features imaginable. In this situation, we knew we wanted to create a course that would ride well top to bottom, but also offer up some opportunities for creativity along the way."⁣
⁣
With the @redbullbike Joyride 10-year anniversary on the near horizon, fans can vote for their favorite feature to be included at Joyride. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Head to our Stories to enter @brandonsemenuk's REALM. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Video By: @revel_co / @redbullbike #RockShox

Hangtime, @hannahbergemann’s women's freeride event, took place this weekend at the Blue Steel jumpline in Bellingham, WA. The event kicked off with the athletes mentoring younger riders through gaining confidence on the bigger jumps, followed by a women's only jump jam open to the public. Head to our stories to watch these women throw down in the full event recap.⁣
⁣
Photos By: @lesliehittmeier / @oliverparish159 #RockShox

node.text:
The Enduro World Series delivered yet another exciting round of tight racing in both the Men's and Women's fields. @isabeau_c found her groove with consistent results in all six stages, leading her to her second gold of her season.⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Having the advantage of winning the Prologue on Saturday, @jackmoir_ came out of the gates chomping at the bit for another win. With three stage wins in Round 6 and two race wins in the past week, Jack continues to pull ahead in the Overall ranking.⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Keeping his bronze streak up, @kevin.miquel sent two for two this weekend claiming the third podium spot. Stay tuned as athletes head to Crans-Montana, Switzerland on September 11-12 for Round 7 of @world_enduro. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Photos By: @maddogboris / @svenmartinphoto #RockShox
